PF set up: list files for PF

Source: R/pf-setup.R
pf_files.Rd

This function creates an ordered list of files for pf_backward_*().

pf_files(.root, ...)

Arguments

.root

A string that defines the directory in which files are located.

...

Additional arguments passed to list.files(), such as pattern, excluding full.names.

Value

The function returns an ordered list of file paths.

See also

TO DO

Author

Edward Lavender

Examples

# Quick implementation of pf_forward()
con <- tempdir()
pff_folder <- file.path(con, "patter", "pf", "forward")
dir.create(pff_folder, recursive = TRUE)
#> Warning: '/var/folders/nl/ygb3g6tj24z06jddbqqhj6hw0000gn/T//RtmpWxc8gS/patter/pf/forward' already exists
out_pff <- pf_forward(.obs = dat_obs(),
                      .bathy = dat_gebco(),
                      .moorings = dat_moorings, .detection_overlaps = dat_overlaps(),
                      .detection_kernels = dat_kernels(),
                      .record_opts = list(sink = pff_folder))
